            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="227" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.Q.1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Preamble</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>Czechoslavakia does not agree with the text of the preamble to the draft Peace
                    Treaty with Hungary because this text makes no mention <pb facs="0738" n="726" xml:id="pg_726"/> of Hungary’s complicity in the preparations for the world
                    war and the dismemberment of Czechoslovakia. Similarly it fails to state that
                    Hungary did not carry on her pre-war policy under pressure but concluded
                    treaties with Italy and Germany of her own free will, voluntarily entered the
                    war on the side of the Axis Powers, and was only forced by the pressure of
                    military events to abandon her alliance with Germany.</p>
                <p>Czechoslovakia therefore reserves the right to present and urge her point of view
                    during the discussion of the Preamble.</p>
            </div>
